    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="871"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d871">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/413.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 12, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Grave embarrassment must ensue unless Liberia makes provision immediately for the
                    retention of monthly sums due Fiscal Agent under loan agreement, which will go
                    into effect as of July 1, 1912. If full receivership not established, have Clark
                    enter into these functions of General Receiver. Insist that Government make the
                    necessary reservations from current income and that these sums be turned over to
                    Clark for eventual transmission to Fiscal Agent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
